        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19309",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mim",
                        "name": "mim",
                        "displayName": "Mark Maynereid",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I just discovered the actual terminology I was groping for is \"boolean attributes\" and in my ignorance missed it in the docs first time round. I thought only the minimised form existed. Here is the HTML reference I should have seen (apols):\n\nhttp:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/html401\/intro\/sgmltut.html#h-3.3.4.2\n\nand here for XHTML:\n\nhttp:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/xhtml1\/#C_10\n\nGoing by the user agent comments, there still might be a case for the patch but I sense not, and I need to get used to writing checked=\"checked\" etc.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mim",
                        "name": "mim",
                        "displayName": "Mark Maynereid",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-20T21:00:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-20T21:00:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19311",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Mark -- you may want to check out recent SVN; the Checkbox element now operates basically as a boolean, and you do not need to specify the 'checked' attribute with it (it determines it based on the value). Let me know if this resolves the issue for you.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-20T21:41:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-20T21:41:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19333",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mim",
                        "name": "mim",
                        "displayName": "Mark Maynereid",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks Matthew. Yes that insulates me from the issue altogether on checkboxes.\n\nI get the impression that ZF general policy is to render the full form boolean attribute so perhaps for a better example where I cannot rely on ZF code deciding, If I want say, a readonly attribute, I should actually set an element's attribute as readonly=readonly for best practice and not worry about  w3.org's browser support for full form booleans as it probably not even a concern any more?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mim",
                        "name": "mim",
                        "displayName": "Mark Maynereid",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-21T09:48:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-21T09:48:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19395",
